<p>
The <code>for</code> keyword in Perl means exactly the same as <code>foreach</code> and
you can use either one interchangeably.
</p>

<p>
<code>$x .. $y</code> is a special operator that returns an array containing the
sequence of consecutive integers from <code>$x</code> up to and including
<code>$y</code>. Now one can fully understand the <code>for $i (1 .. 10)</code>
construct that we used in the beginning of this lecture.
</p>
